  hours here — that is business-data.md's job, not the vault's.

Decision rule for any new fact you learn: if it is today's operational truth
(a price, an hour, what's on the menu right now), it belongs in
business-data.md, not the vault. If it is a durable, structured fact about a
specific customer, supplier, or recurring pattern that is worth being able to
find and read again later, write or update a note under `/home/hermes/vault/`
(see `/home/hermes/vault/README.md` for the layout). If it is just useful
context for the rest of this conversation and not worth a dedicated note,
Mnemosyne is enough — you do not need to also write a vault note for it.

